{
  "texts": [
    "They employed CNN for sentence representation and LSTM for document representation, enabling the capture of contexts from both individual sentences and the entire document.",
    "Furthermore, attention pooling was utilized after the convolutional layer and LSTM layer to identify the relevant words and sentences within the essay.",
    "Augmenting text quality features: Instead of solely focusing on word and sentence representation in essays, several studies have shown the impact of incorporating additional features to enhance the performance of AES model (Dasgupta et al. 2018; Liang et al. 2018).",
    "Dasgupta et al. (2018) proposed qualitatively enhanced convolutional recurrent neural net-",
    "The essay representation column shows that feature representation mechanism, such as representing as sequence of words (SW), hierarchical document structure(DM), using coherence modeling (CM), incorporating handcrafted features (HF) and incorporating rating features (RF) 1 3 works that learn from both latent linguistic characteristics of the essay and automatically identified complex patterns using neural networks."
  ]
